[src:custom-elements/api-window] Returns a reference to the current window.
[src:custom-elements/api-window] Returns a reference to the `window` object in the frames.
[src:custom-elements/api-window] If a property corresponds to a single element, that element is directly returned.
[src:custom-elements/api-window] If the property corresponds to multiple elements, then an `HTMLCollection` is returned containing all of them.
[src:custom-elements/api-window] If any of the elements is a navigable `<iframe>` or `<object>`, then the `contentWindow` of first such iframe is returned instead.
[src:custom-elements/api-window] Returns the **current event**, which is the event currently being handled by the JavaScript code's context, or `undefined` if no event is currently being handled.
[src:custom-elements/api-window] The `Event` object passed directly to event handlers should be used instead whenever possible.
[src:custom-elements/api-window] Returns an object with functions for adding external search providers to the browser.
[src:custom-elements/api-window] Returns the orientation in degrees (in 90 degree increments) of the viewport relative to the device's natural orientation.
